author: CNN
description: The White House has installed new plaques along President Donald Trump's "Presidential Walk of Fame," featuring descriptions that read like his Truth Social posts, including insults and random capitalization. CNN's Kaitlan Collins reports from the White House.
title: Trump displays new plaques at 'Presidential Walk of Fame'

author: CNN
description: A Statue of Liberty replica in southern Brazil toppled over after the city experienced high winds. No one was injured in the collapse. #brazil #cnn
title: Statue of Liberty replica collapses in Brazil

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump announced that he will deliver a live address from the White House tonight. CNN's Kristen Holmes explains what that could entail.
title: Trump to address nation from White House tonight

author: CNN
description: Lawler and three other House Republicans bucked their party to join with Democrats and force a vote on a three-year extension of Obamacare subsidies.   #CNN #News #politics
title: President Trump to give prime-time speech amid new cracks in GOP support

author: CNN
description: Former special counsel Jack Smith on Wednesday defended his criminal investigation into President Donald Trump in a closed-door deposition before the House Judiciary Committee as he faces scrutiny from Republican lawmakers. Smith was called to testify about Trump’s alleged mishandling and retention of classified documents and his role in attempting to overturn the 2020 election, according to sources familiar with the investigation.  #CNN #News
title: Jack Smith testifies he decided to charge Trump based on the president’s actions

author: CNN
description: GOP centrists in the House just agreed to help Democrats force a vote on their own bill which would extend Obamacare subsidies. CNN’s Manu Raju reports.
title: GOP centrists make hardball play against Speaker Mike Johnson

author: CNN
description: CNN accompanies the Ugandan opposition leader as he tries to campaign ahead of the country's presidential elections in January 2026. But everywhere Bobi Wine goes, there are dozens of police officers, soldiers, stopping him from moving about and beating supporters. #CNN #News
title: ‘This is war’ on Uganda’s campaign trail

author: CNN
description: Nick Reiner appeared briefly in court today after being charged with two counts of first-degree murder in connection with the fatal stabbing of his parents, Hollywood director Rob Reiner and producer Michele Singer Reiner. He also faces a special allegation that he used a knife, according to the Los Angeles County District Attorney’s Office.  #CNN #News
title: Nick Reiner makes first court appearance after being charged with murdering his parents

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jake Tapper explains why the Brown University shooting wasn't captured on camera.
title: Why wasn't Brown University shooting captured on camera?

author: CNN
description: In a stunning blow to House Speaker Mike Johnson, four GOP lawmakers have agreed to back a Democratic push to extend pandemic-era enhanced Obamacare subsidies. Those four GOP centrists — New York Rep. Mike Lawler and Pennsylvania Reps. Brian Fitzpatrick, Ryan Mackenzie and Rob Bresnahan — have officially opted for what they have been describing as the nuclear option. CNN's Manu Raju reports. #CNN #News
title: GOP centrists defy Speaker Johnson by backing Dems’ push to extend Obamacare subsidies

author: CNN
description: Vanity Fair writer Chris Whipple, who interviewed White House Chief of Staff Susie Wiles and multiple other top Trump administration officials, defends his reporting after the White House’s criticism. In the interview, Wiles was unusually candid and offered at times unflattering assessments of President Donald Trump, his second-term agenda and some of his closest allies. #cnn #news
title: Journalist behind bombshell Wiles interview responds to criticism

author: CNN
description:
Authorities are still searching for the perpetrator of the deadly mass shooting at Brown University. Local police released new “enhanced” videos of a person of interest, and the FBI released a video timeline. CNN's Brian Todd reports. 

#cnn #news #brown #rhodeisland
title: New “enhanced” video of the person of interest in the Brown shooting released

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said Tuesday he was ordering a “total and complete blockade” of sanctioned oil tankers coming to and leaving from Venezuela, ratcheting up pressure against leader Nicolás Maduro’s regime and suggesting an economic motive to the US’ military campaign in the region.  #CNN #News
title: Trump orders blockade of sanctioned oil tankers coming to and leaving Venezuela

author: CNN
description: Radio transmissions reviewed by CNN show that the pilots of a private jet narrowly avoided a collision with a United States Air Force refueling tanker near Venezuela on Saturday – one day after a similar incident nearby. The pilots of a Falcon 900EX business jet flying from Aruba to Miami reported the near collision to air traffic controllers in Curaçao shortly after the incident Saturday afternoon, according to audio captured by LiveATC.net. CNN's Pete Muntean reports.  #CNN #News
title: Second near midair collision with US military aircraft reported near Venezuela

author: CNN
description: The suspects behind the Bondi Beach attack traveled to the Philippines last month, to a region long known as a hotbed for Islamic extremism and insurgency. Authorities are now investigating whether the trip was linked to the attack. CNN's Jessie Yeung reports.
title: Alleged Bondi shooters visited Philippine region known for extremism

author: CNN
description: A two-part series from Vanity Fair features new interviews with WH Chief of Staff Susie Wiles, where she gives her take on the people she works with, including Pres. Trump, who she says has an “alcoholic’s personality.” Vanity Fair writer Chris Whipple talks about the reaction.  #CNN #News
title: Vanity Fair writer on WIles: ‘Every interview was recorded, everything was on tape’

author: CNN
description: In an exclusive interview with CNN’s Kaitlan Collins, Republican Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene said that President Trump’s recent remarks about the murder of director Rob Reiner and his wife were “completely below the office of the president of the United States.”  #CNN #News
title: Marjorie Taylor Greene calls Trump’s reaction to Reiner’s death ‘classless’

author: CNN
description: Parents of the youngest victim of the Sydney terror attacks, 10-year-old Matilda, recall the moments leading up to her killing on Sunday.
title: Funerals take place after Sydney terror attack

author: CNN
description: Two years after she went missing in Tasmania's wilderness, a search party found the phone of Celine Cremer, who went missing in June 2023. Police now theorize she left the marked trail to try and reach her car before darkness fell and become disorientated.
title: Missing hiker's phone found two years after disappearance

author: CNN
description:
Description: In an exclusive report, CNN’s Nada Bashir in collaboration with investigative newsroom Lighthouse Reports, uncovers a chilling chain of events in Sudan’s civil war. 

This video contains imagery viewers may find disturbing. 

Read the full investigation at CNN.com: https://cnn.it/49fbMQW
title: Satellite imagery and whistleblowers reveal bodies in Sudan’s canals

author: CNN
description: President Trump ordered a “total and complete blockade” of sanctioned oil tankers coming to and leaving from Venezuela, announcing the move in a Truth Social post that escalated his rhetoric against Venezuelan leader Nicolas Maduro’s regime. #cnn #news
title: Trump’s blockade could lead to regime change in Venezuela - analyst says

author: CNN
description: FBI Director Kash Patel is being criticized over the timing of a podcast interview he and his girlfriend, singer Alexis Wilkins, gave to conservative political advisor Katie Miller amid an ongoing FBI manhunt for the Brown University shooting suspect.
title: Kash Patel dragged over interview with girlfriend

author: CNN
description: Disney’s animated film “Zootopia 2” was such a hit in China that some young people are buying poisonous snakes. CNN speaks to an owner of an Indonesian pit viper to find out why he decided to buy the blue reptile. #CNN #News #Zootopia2
title: ‘Zootopia 2’ has Chinese young people buying venomous snakes

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump condemned the Bondi Beach shooting as antisemitic at the White House Hanukkah Reception. #cnn #news #trump #hanukkah #bondibeach
title: Trump condemns antisemitism after Bondi Beach shooting

author: CNN
description: Nick Reiner has been charged with two counts of first-degree murder in connection with the fatal stabbing of his parents, Michele and Rob Reiner. He's currently being held without bail. Photos show Los Angeles Police and US Marshals arresting Nick Reiner on Sunday night. The LAPD's gang and narcotics division initially posted the images to their official Instagram account but deleted them later. When CNN reached out to the LAPD to ask why the images were deleted, the department didn't comment on them.
title: Source tells CNN details of Nick Reiner at Conan O'Brien's party

author: CNN
description: In an exclusive interview with CNN's Kaitlan Collins, Republican Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene said that President Trump’s recent remarks about the murder of director Rob Reiner and his wife were “completely below the office of the president of the United States."
title: Marjorie Taylor Greene calls Trump's reaction to Reiner's death 'classless'

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump said Monday that the White House is “very strongly” considering signing an executive order to reschedule marijuana to a lower drug classification, which would ease federal restrictions.

CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down public opinion. #CNN #News
title: CNN's Harry Enten looks at changing attitudes toward legalizing marijuana

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump defended his chief of staff Susie Wiles after Vanity Fair published her candid and at times unflattering assessments of the president and some of his closest allies, telling the New York Post she “has done a fantastic job.” CNN's Kasie Hunt describes what Republicans are saying behind closed doors.
title: What Republicans are saying privately about explosive Vanity Fair interview

author: CNN
description:
In 1975 Kelsey Grammer’s 18-year-old sister, Karen, was murdered. For fifty years his loving memories of her were colored by questions about her death. In this moving conversation, Kelsey tells Anderson how he finally found answers and, in doing so, the beloved sister he lost so long ago. This conversation contains some graphic descriptions of violence.

Join the community to share your story and watch Anderson's weekly streaming show All There Is Live at https://cnn.com/allthereis
title: Kelsey Grammer on reclaiming the memory of his sister fifty years after her murder

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump sued the BBC on Monday for defamation over edited clips of a speech that made it appear he directed supporters to storm the US Capitol, opening an international front in his fight against media coverage he deems untrue or unfair.
title: Trump sues BBC for billions

author: CNN
description:
Authorities have received hundreds of tips in the investigation of Saturday’s mass shooting, Oscar L. Perez Jr., the chief of the Providence, Rhode Island, police department. In a new collection of videos released by the Providence Police Department, authorities are asking the public to pay attention to body movements, posture, gait and other patterns to help identify the person of interest, Perez said in a Tuesday news conference.

Jake Tapper speaks with CNN chief law enforcement and intelligence analyst John Miller and CNN senior national security analyst Juliette Kayyem. #CNN #News
title: Authorities give update in Brown University killings, ask public to watch new videos
